definition.value: A LinkML schema implementing CIDOC-CRM-aligned classes, event-centric patterns, and provenance for Nepal cultural heritage linked open data.
Actor: individuals, groups or organisations involved in events.
Project place specialization with common slots.

An event that modifies an object.
Superclass for all physical things including monuments, artefacts, buildings and parts.
Spatial and temporal extent used for precise spatio-temporal modelling (site extents, archaeological layers).
Designs, procedures or protocols (restoration workflows, ritual procedures).

Concepts, schemes, records, and textual objects carrying information.
